Key Match Events: Austria scored an own goal by Donyell Malen in the 6th minute.
Cody Gakpo equalized for the Netherlands in the 23rd minute.
Romano Schmid scored for Austria in the 59th minute.
Marcel Sabitzer scored the winning goal for Austria in the 80th minute.
Post-Match Reflections: Marcel Sabitzer praised the team's effort and said winning the group is the most important thing.
Dutch captain Virgil van Dijk criticized the team's performance and possession issues.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Austria's win and group top spot were a surprise result.
The match was played at Olympiastadion Berlin with 68,363 attendees.
Wout Weghorst came on as a substitute and set up a chance for Memphis Depay.
